claim.claim-text:
1. An inkjet recording apparatus for ejecting ink through nozzles onto a recording medium, comprising:
a nozzle head having a nozzle surface in which at least two nozzles are provided;
an absorber configured to abut the nozzle surface to absorb ink adhered on the nozzle surface, a portion of the absorber which corresponds to openings of the nozzles being removed such that the absorber is configured to abut the nozzle surface except for a region near the nozzles;
an actuator configured to move the absorber at least one of to the nozzle surface and from the nozzle surface; and
a cap provided at the portion from which the absorber is removed, the cap coming in close contact with the nozzle surface to cover the openings of the nozzles when the absorber abuts the nozzle surface.

3. An inkjet recording apparatus for ejecting ink through nozzles onto a recording medium, comprising:
a nozzle head having a nozzle surface in which at least two nozzles are provided;
an absorber configured to abut the nozzle surface to absorb ink adhered on the nozzle surface, a portion of the absorber which corresponds to openings of the nozzles being removed such that the absorber is configured to abut the nozzle surface except for a region near the nozzles;
an actuator configured to move the absorber at least one of to the nozzle surface and from the nozzle surface; and
a cap provided at the portion from which the absorber is removed, the cap coming in close contact with the nozzle surface to cover the openings of the nozzles when the absorber abuts the nozzle surface,
wherein at least two said nozzle heads are arranged along the width direction of the recording medium to constitute a line head.
